<Plain
  title="Privacy policy — OpenAlarm"
  description="OpenAlarm collects no data. What the app's permissions are used for."
  heading="Privacy policy"
>
  <p>OpenAlarm does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data. There are no accounts, no analytics, no tracking, and no third-party services.</p>

  <p>Everything the app knows — your alarms, settings, and challenge configuration — stays on your device (and in your device backups, which you control).</p>

  <p>Permissions the app asks for are used only for the feature they enable: notifications and alarms so your alarm can ring, Motion &amp; Fitness for the Steps and Shake challenges, and the camera for the Scan challenge. Camera frames are processed on-device and never stored or uploaded.</p>

  <p>This website is a static page and sets no cookies.</p>

  <p>Questions? Open an issue on GitHub (<a href="https://github.com/gretzke/open-alarm/issues">github.com/gretzke/open-alarm/issues</a>) or email <a href="mailto:support@tryopenalarm.com">support@tryopenalarm.com</a>.</p>
</Plain>
